01:04.772 --> 01:09.449
Ever wonder about all these militia groups,
survivalist-type kooks on the right-wing side?

01:09.611 --> 01:13.332
They say that they're defending
the country from the U.N. troops.

01:13.490 --> 01:18.041
These guys yelling so loud, my theory
is... And this is a conspiracy, pal.

01:18.245 --> 01:20.213
They are the U.N. troops.
They're in place!

01:20.372 --> 01:22.625
The infrastructure's ready.
It's a <i>fait accompli.</i>

01:22.791 --> 01:24.793
They'll just take over.
We'll all be toast.

01:24.960 --> 01:27.429
Oswald. Yeah, that's
what I said, Oswald.

01:27.588 --> 01:31.013
He said, "I'm just a patsy."
That means he didn't do it, right?

01:31.174 --> 01:33.597
Armand Hammer goes to the doctor.

01:33.760 --> 01:35.808
The doctor says, "Hey, Armand..."

01:35.971 --> 01:37.769
you've only got 3 minutes to live."

01:37.931 --> 01:40.104
And he says, "Oh, God,
that's terrible news."

01:40.267 --> 01:43.396
Isn't there anything you can do
for me, doc? Three minutes?"

01:43.562 --> 01:46.156
And the doctor says,
"Well, I can boil you an egg."

01:47.608 --> 01:50.111
I guess not. All right.

01:50.277 --> 01:53.156
Do you ever see those
advertisements, like, "Got Milk?"

01:53.322 --> 01:54.824
(TIRES SCREECHING)

01:57.534 --> 02:00.333
Hey, Open up! Open it up!

02:00.495 --> 02:02.964
What's going on in there?
Open it up.

02:03.123 --> 02:05.046
Son of a bitch!

02:05.959 --> 02:07.131
JERRY: "Eat beef"?

02:07.294 --> 02:12.050
That's like saying, "Smoke cigarettes,"
or "Drive cars." I mean, it's real generic.

02:12.215 --> 02:15.890
This guy looks at me and says, "You
think you're living in a free country?"

02:16.053 --> 02:18.602
"You think it's a democracy?
Of course it's not."

02:18.764 --> 02:22.189
Web sites, newsletters,
self-published manifestos.

02:22.351 --> 02:23.694
They think we're kooks.

02:23.852 --> 02:27.231
George Bush knew what he was saying
when he said, "New World Order."

02:27.397 --> 02:29.445
You remember those
three little words?

02:29.608 --> 02:34.034
He was a 33rd degree Mason, you know,
and as ex-director of the CIA...

02:34.196 --> 02:37.416
he knew that saying that would send
conspiratologists everywhere...

02:37.574 --> 02:39.793
spinning, spinning their wheels.

02:39.951 --> 02:41.874
Then they destroy their
own credibility.

02:42.037 --> 02:45.587
Don't get me wrong, sister, I'm sure
your heart's in the right place...

02:45.749 --> 02:49.970
but, you know, somebody's got to lift
the festering scab that is the Vatican.

02:52.464 --> 02:56.310
A chip for identification so they can
track down an animal anywhere he's at.

02:56.468 --> 03:00.223
You'll insert it under the dog's skin
and it's an identification thing.

03:00.389 --> 03:03.518
I mean, it's only a
small logical step...

03:03.684 --> 03:07.188
until they start putting it in us and
our children. Before we know it...

03:07.354 --> 03:08.606
(DOG BARKING)

03:08.772 --> 03:10.866
they'll probably come
with the pretext...

03:11.024 --> 03:15.245
Sure. Hey, is that one of the new hundreds
where they changed picture of Ben Franklin?

03:15.404 --> 03:16.951
Look at him. He looks like...

03:17.114 --> 03:20.118
the love child of Fred
Mertz and Rosie O'Donnell.

03:20.283 --> 03:23.162
Yeah, that's him. Get rid of
them as soon as you can, lady.

03:23.328 --> 03:26.582
Look at it. See the metal strip in it?
That's a tracking device.

03:26.748 --> 03:30.548
If you got any more of those at home,
get rid of them. Exchange them.

03:30.711 --> 03:34.841
They'll follow you. They know where
every one of those hundreds is going...

03:37.300 --> 03:40.429
Black helicopters. You heard
about them? The black helicopters?

03:40.595 --> 03:42.347
They're... They're everywhere.

03:43.390 --> 03:47.987
They're on whisper mode. You can't
hear them until they've already gone.

03:48.145 --> 03:49.567
You know?

03:52.649 --> 03:55.698
No. There's nobody there.
Where did...? Where did they...?

03:55.861 --> 03:59.081
Where'd they go? Oh, there
was nobody in here! Nobody.

03:59.239 --> 04:01.662
What am I talking...?
Why is the meter on?

04:04.786 --> 04:06.333
MAN: Taxi!

04:06.621 --> 04:07.668
(WHISTLES)

04:07.831 --> 04:09.458
Taxi!

04:22.971 --> 04:25.394
- Where to, pal?
- Luxembourg Towers, on 7th.

04:25.557 --> 04:27.184
Okay.

04:35.275 --> 04:36.822
(MAN SIGHS)

04:39.446 --> 04:41.119
The sound of love.

04:41.281 --> 04:42.533
Excuse me?

04:42.699 --> 04:44.042
That, what you just did.

04:44.201 --> 04:45.544
(SIGHS)

04:45.702 --> 04:47.170
- That's love.
- Heh.

04:47.329 --> 04:49.957
"Love is just a way of saying,
"I want to sleep with you."

04:50.123 --> 04:52.296
Admit it. I saw you kiss her.

04:52.459 --> 04:55.008
You love her. This is the
street where love lives.

04:55.170 --> 04:57.389
Love is bullshit.

04:58.423 --> 05:00.391
Love gives you wings.

05:00.550 --> 05:02.552
It makes you fly.

05:03.053 --> 05:04.680
I don't even call it love.

05:05.430 --> 05:07.182
I call it "Geronimo."

05:07.891 --> 05:09.518
- MAN: Geronimo?
- Yeah.

05:09.684 --> 05:12.062
Geronimo. See, when
you're in love, you'll...

05:12.229 --> 05:15.699
jump right from the top of the
Empire State and you won't care.

05:15.857 --> 05:19.361
Screaming "Geronimo" the whole
way down. It's great.

05:19.528 --> 05:22.873
Yeah, but then you'll die. You'll squash
yourself. So, what's the point?

05:23.031 --> 05:26.035
Hey, aren't you listening? I'm
telling you, love gives you wings.

05:26.201 --> 05:27.327
(CHUCKLES)

05:27.494 --> 05:30.043
She must be some girl.

05:30.914 --> 05:33.008
I love her so bad, I just...

05:33.166 --> 05:35.214
Well, she wrecks me.

05:37.587 --> 05:39.464
I'd die for her.

05:42.884 --> 05:45.353
(WORKER SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

05:46.596 --> 05:48.348
MAN: She feel the same about you?

05:49.391 --> 05:51.564
JERRY: I don't know.

05:52.602 --> 05:55.446
Uh, I never told her.

05:55.605 --> 05:56.822
MAN: Why the hell not?

06:01.403 --> 06:03.155
Uh...

06:04.948 --> 06:07.121
I have some problems.

06:16.543 --> 06:18.671
